lowest level in almost three months on concern that the cut in
the U.S. credit rating by  Standard & Poorâ€™s  will curb the global
economic recovery.  Metal for three-month delivery on the London Metal Exchange
fell as much as 1.4 percent to $8,661 a metric ton, the lowest
